{"name":"Flagellant","permission":{"default":0,"IJqIDe1c5JlxpePC":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You have dedicated your pain to the service of your God. Each day, you must spend half a bell (half an hour) praying as you maintain a number of Wounds su?ered equal to your level in Flagellant. Until you next sleep, if you have the Frenzy Talent you may enter Frenzy immediately without testing.</p>\n<p>Additionally, you may flagellate yourself further, and repent for your Sins by removing a further number of Wounds equal to your current Sin Points, when you do the above. Doing so removes 1 Sin Point. Pain is sadly slow but effective path to redemption.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"t"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":"Any for resisting the Ruinous Powers"},"source":{"type":"String","label":"Source"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/wfrp4e-content/icons/talents/flagellant.png","_id":"IW3f6vqRg5Q21gno"}
{"name":"Holy Hatred","permission":{"default":0,"IJqIDe1c5JlxpePC":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>Your prayers drip with the hatred you feel for your blasphemous enemies. You deal +1 Damage with Miracles for each level in this Talent.</p>\n<p>Additionally, after using Pray to meditate in Combat for +1 Advantage, you may immediately perform an attack against an opponent, including a Charge if required, with your full Advantage. Whether successful or not, all of your Advantage is removed after this Free Attack.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"fel"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":"Pray when Meditating in Combat"},"source":{"type":"String","label":"Source"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/wfrp4e-content/icons/talents/holy-hatred.png","_id":"JSJg7UUBqtdIq8Ff"}
{"name":"Bad Luck","permission":{"default":0,"IJqIDe1c5JlxpePC":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>Tests the knight makes that rely on luck (rather than skill) suffer a -1 SL penalty.</p>\n<p>Whenever a character with Bad Luck spends a Fortune Point, an <em>unlucky inconvenience</em> also occurs. The added <em>unlucky inconvenience</em> is never deadly (directly), and doesn&rsquo;t necessarily affect just the knight, though it will always affect at least the knight. Distance from the knight doesn&rsquo;t matter, as long as the <em>unlucky inconvenience</em> affects the knight as well.</p>\n<p>Rather than being a talent that the devotee purchases to obtain, Bad Luck is a talent the devotee pays to remove (the XP cost is the same). However, if and when the devotee pays off the Bad Luck, they in turn gain the<strong> Nose for Trouble</strong> Talent. unfortunately, the knight must endure a period of service to the Order encumbered by Bad Luck that is equal to their Wounds in months before they can remove Bad Luck.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"1"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":"Any test that relies on luck"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/divine-careers/Icons/Talents/Bad%20Luck.png","_id":"Qkzu29WrSqoXPXxc"}
{"name":"Merciful Presence","permission":{"default":0,"IJqIDe1c5JlxpePC":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>Your presence fills others with hushed awe and admiration. Such is your aura of mercy, those with a lower Status may not resist your Leadership tests withtheir Willpower..</p>\n<p>You may also comfort the sick or wounded and bring peaceful absolution to the dying, gracing them with<em> peace of mind</em> which lasts your WPB x 1d10 minutes. This peace of mind grants the patient <em>Immunity to Fear (any)</em>, ushering them gently into the care of Morr for restful sleep and respite from pain or eternal slumber.</p>\n<p><em>Merciful Presence</em> only works if the initiate is revealed or known to be a Shallyan and only if the person being impressed understands what Shallya represents.</p>\n<p>In any follower of Nurgle, it causes <em>Hatred (the initiate)</em>.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"wp"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":"Leadership"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/divine-careers/Icons/Talents/Merciful%20Presence.png","_id":"t67Zql28HZE4H3Uo"}
{"name":"Child of Ulric","permission":{"default":0,"IJqIDe1c5JlxpePC":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>Once per day, the initiate may transform into a Child of Ulric, a special blessed type of Were: for more on Children of Ulric refer to Weres on the Road or use the Wolf profile (WFRP p. 317), adding the Champion, Elite, and Frenzy traits and removing the Bestial and Skittish traits.</p>\n<p><strong>This talent requires that the initiate </strong><strong>already possesses the Blessed Talent.</strong></p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"1"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/divine-careers/Icons/Talents/Child%20of%20Ulric.png","_id":"zNirkmxUfpmLYVQx"}
